<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-8708] SOAP unmarshalling shouldn&apos;t fail for Faults that lack an optional Detail element</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-8708</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Camel-soap code assumes that all Faults that a Camel SOAP endpoint is receiving, are containing a Detail element. Sending a Fault without Detail will result in an NPE. Detail is optional element in SOAP Faults (see &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/soap12-part1/#soapfault&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.w3.org/TR/soap12-part1/#soapfault&lt;/a&gt;) and its absence should not generate an error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12824339">CAMEL-8708</key>
            <summary>SOAP unmarshalling shouldn&apos;t fail for Faults that lack an optional Detail element</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
